  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      According to the WHO, therapeutic education is intended to help patients acquire or maintain
      the skills they need to optimally manage living with a chronic disease. Low back pain is
      frequent and therapeutic education could be a promising option.

      The purpose of the study is to evaluate the impact of a therapeutic education program for
      patients suffering from low back pain.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
